data.title: Stoute stumped by Golan failure

data.text:
SIR MICHAEL STOUTE left Melbourne for home yesterday, disappointed by the Cup run of Daliapour but bearing two more profound regrets. Remarkably, Stoute had never been to Australia before and he confided: “I wish I’d come 20 years ago. I’d also love to have stayed on to see some cricket but I need to get back and make some decisions about the rest of the year.”

Stoute, who has enjoyed his most prolific domestic season for some years, is keen to seek further international laurels with Golan in the Japan Cup on November 24. “We want to run him but it is still a mystery why he ran so badly in the Breeders’ Cup,” he said. “He had been so well going into the race
